#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/management-structure.xml:40
#, no-wrap
msgid "What was the purpose of the new management structure?"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:44
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The purpose of the new management structure was to solve chronic\n"
"management, coordination and communication issues in the Gentoo project. In\n"
"particular, we had no clearly defined top-level management structure, and no\n"
"official, regular meetings to communicate status updates between developers\n"
"serving in critical roles. In general, most communication took place on irc\n"
"and irregularly via email. There was also little to no accountability, even\n"
"at a high level, to complete projects on time.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:54
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Because of this prior state of affairs, it was difficult to set goals and\n"
"track the status of projects. This lack of communication and coordination\n"
"also made it difficult for top-level developers to manage their own\n"
"projects. In addition, we had other chronic problem of not having\n"
"clearly-defined roles and scopes of executive decision-making authority for\n"
"top-level developers, which resulted in many top-level developers doubting\n"
"that they even have the authority to manage their own projects and\n"
"sub-projects. While this had *never* been the intention of top-level\n"
"developers, it is the unfortunate result of an unstructured development\n"
"process: no one knew what was going on, and everyone deferred to the Chief\n"
"Architect for all executive decisions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:68
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Clearly, a plan was needed to swiftly and permanently address these issues by\n"
"increasing communication, coordination, and accountability. Roles and scopes\n"
"of executive decision-making authority needed to be defined for top developers\n"
"so that they have a clear mandate as well as accountability to manage their\n"
"projects and thus ensure their projects completed their appointed work\n"
"efficiently and on-schedule.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/management-structure.xml:79
#, no-wrap
msgid "Initial implementation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:83
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Initial implementation of the new management structure began by creating\n"
"official top-level management structure. This management structure consists\n"
"of the Chief Architect and a group of developers that will be given the title\n"
"of Top-level Managers. Top-level Managers will be accountable for the\n"
"projects they manage, and be responsible for communicating the status of\n"
"their projects to the rest of the Top-level Managers and Chief Architect,\n"
"as well as other responsibilities detailed later in this document.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:93
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"All the top-level projects in the Gentoo project are in the process of\n"
"being clearly defined, including goals, sub-projects, members, roadmap and\n"
"schedules.  The \"Hardened Gentoo\" page at\n"
"<uri>http://www.gentoo.org/proj/en/hardened/</uri> is an excellent example\n"
"of such a top-level project definition, and many other top-level projects\n"
"currently exist today.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:102
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Certain executive decision-making authority will be granted to these\n"
"projects, as agreed upon by the Chief Architect, Top-level Managers and\n"
"project members.  Then, as part of the initial implementation of the new\n"
"management structure, a Top-level Manager or managers will be officially\n"
"adopt projects and ebuild herds.  These managers will be responsible for\n"
"tracking the status of the project, ensuring that the project meets targets\n"
"and is generally managed properly.  Manager responsibilities are described\n"
"in detail later in this document.\n"
msgstr ""

