#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/management-structure.xml:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "Management charter"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:140
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1) Constructive, professional communication: All communication should be\n"
"focused on improving the management of Gentoo projects, should be\n"
"constructive in nature and should be shared in a friendly, professional\n"
"manner.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:147
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"2) Accountability to peers: Allow fellow members of this list to hold us\n"
"accountable to follow-through on projects and meet deadlines. Keep fellow\n"
"members accountable.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:153
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3) Management of projects: empower managers to have the authority and\n"
"strategic direction necessary to properly manage thier projects and efforts\n"
"to ensure projects complete their appointed work on time.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:159
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"4) Results: our expectation is that our efforts, when properly executed,\n"
"will result in the Gentoo project's ability to meet deadlines, have much\n"
"better communication and coordination throughout the entire project, higher\n"
"overall quality and a more positive experience for all.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/management-structure.xml:168
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manager responsibilities"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:172
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Every top-level Gentoo project will have a clearly defined scope, and\n"
"clearly defined and explicit executive decision-making authority that will\n"
"be granted to managers of the project to exercise and/or delegate as they\n"
"see fit. Both the scope and any necessary decision-making authority must be\n"
"agreed upon by both the Chief Architect and project members. The scope and\n"
"executive authority of a project can be expanded over time as required as\n"
"approved by the Top-level Managers and Chief Architect.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"In addition to decision-making authority, managers have the following\n"
"responsibilities:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:188
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Keep a complete list of all projects and efforts you are managing,\n"
"    and associated gentoo.org project page up-to-date\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:193
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Manage and track the status of these efforts. This includes active\n"
"    direction as well as passive tracking of progress.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:198
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Define clear goals, roadmaps and timelines (preliminary if necessary) for\n"
"    every effort.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:202
#, no-wrap
msgid "Proactively identify efforts that have problems and need help."
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:205
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Ensure that your efforts are completed on-time, or that any efforts that\n"
"    are behind-schedule are reported in a timely manner.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:210
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Remain focused. Make sure that you are not managing more than you can\n"
"    handle.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:215
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Fulfill formal communication and coordination responsibilities required by\n"
"    top-level managers (weekly meetings, etc.)\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:220
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    Fulfill formal communication and coordination responsibilities required\n"
"    by individual efforts (project meetings, communication with project members,\n"
"    etc.) This is important as our management of projects means that we\n"
"    have the responsibility not only to communicate with our peers but\n"
"    also those who we are managing. This communication should be frequent,\n"
"    have a formal component (planned meetings, official status updates,\n"
"    etc.) and model good management practices to members of our teams.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><ol><li>
#: en/management-structure.xml:230
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"    <b>RECURSIVE FUNCTIONALITY</b>: At an appropriate time, implement these\n"
"    management practices for *sub*-projects (define managers, clear sub-project\n"
"    goals, grant executive authority) with you serving as primary authority.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/management-structure.xml:239
#, no-wrap
msgid "Meetings, logs and status updates"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:243
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Currently, weekly manager meetings are held on irc, and all Gentoo developers\n"
"are welcome to join the meeting channel and view the meeting in progress. In\n"
"addition, after the meeting completes, the floor is opened for questions and\n"
"comments by developers. The weekly meetings generally take place on\n"
"Monday. After the meeting and open-floor session is concluded, a log of the\n"
"meeting is posted to the gentoo-core mailing list.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:252
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Status updates are very important to the proper functioning of our\n"
"management structure. Currently, managers make an effort to email each other\n"
"weekly status updates. Soon, we hope to post weekly status updates to our\n"
"respective project pages so that the public can be apprised on the status of\n"
"every top-level project.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><note>
#: en/management-structure.xml:260
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Inability to attend due to time zone can be addressed by posting\n"
"the full IRC log to gentoo-managers and allowing non-attending members\n"
"to post ideas, comments and follow-ups.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><title>
#: en/management-structure.xml:268
#, no-wrap
msgid "Decision-making"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:272
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Currently, GLEPs (Gentoo Linux Enhancement Proposals) can be approved or\n"
"rejected by the appropriate top-level manager under which the GLEP falls. If\n"
"there is no clearly-defined manager under which the GLEP falls, the GLEP will be\n"
"voted upon by the Managers and Chief Architect, and must be approved\n"
"unanimously. In all cases, a public, written explanation must be provided\n"
"detailing why the GLEP was approved or rejected, either by the manager who\n"
"approved/rejected it, or the head of the GLEP sub-project (Grant Goodyear) if\n"
"the GLEP was voted upon by the management team. This summary is meant to reflect\n"
"the decision that was made by some of the managers at an early manager meeting.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:284
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Currently, there is no formal general voting procedure in place. In the interim,\n"
"any item to be voted upon must be approved by \"votable\" by the Chief Architect.\n"
"Before voting takes place, all managers must have an opportunity to present\n"
"their ideas before the other managers, with the general originator(s) of the\n"
"idea having the opportunity to present first. After that, the Chief Architect\n"
"and Managers can present their ideas, with the Chief Architect having the\n"
"opportunity to present last. After this has happened, voting can take place, and\n"
"the item will be approved on an unanimous vote. Managers or the Chief Architect\n"
"can choose to abstain from voting, and the vote can still pass with abstainers\n"
"as long as at least 50% of the members have voted. The voting must take place at\n"
"an official managers meeting. Non-attending managers are allowed to vote via\n"
"email. The vote must be officially tallied and posted to the managers list.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:299
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The reason for the \"Chief Architect approval\" clause it to prevent the voting\n"
"process from being abused by allowing voting items that make no sense, such as\n"
"those that begin with a \"Should we continue to,\" where a \"nay\" result would\n"
"result in a change in existing policy, as well as preventing managers for\n"
"requesting that every small decision be voted upon. We currently have no clear\n"
"policy to determine what is a \"votable\" item, and without this policy there\n"
"needs to be some method to determine what is \"votable\" and what affects some\n"
"immutable part of Gentoo.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Content of: <guide><chapter><section><body><p>
#: en/management-structure.xml:310
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"This section is subject to additional clarification and refinement in the\n"
"future, as is the rest of this document. The purpose of this section is to\n"
"document our currently-existing procedures rather than define ideal or \"final\"\n"
"procedures.\n"
msgstr ""

